b'Summer Medical Research Training Program for College Students'
b'Home'
b'Education'
b'Programs for High School and College Students'
b'caherman'
b'Summer Medical Research Training (SMaRT) Program'
b'The University of Illinois College of Medicine Rockford SMaRT\xc2\xa0Program\xc2\xa0is an internship opportunity for undergraduate college students from around the country that allows them to interact closely with professionals in either an academic or industrial research environment. Students selected for this eight-week program gain valuable hands-on laboratory skills using a variety of scientific techniques.'
b'Each summer, approximately three students are selected to complete an eight-week research internship program in medical research at the basic research laboratories of the UIC Health Sciences Campus-Rockford.\xc2\xa0During this training, the students gain significant hands-on experience in planning and successfully executing a medical research project. Working closely with various research faculty and staff, the students gain expertise in cutting-edge techniques and\xc2\xa0their application in biomedical research. At the conclusion of the program, students present their scientific data as a poster and an oral presentation at the college\xe2\x80\x99s SMaRT Scientific Forum. Students receive a stipend at the end of the program.'
b'The SMaRT program is a highly competitive program. Students are selected based on their academic merit, a personal interview and their interest in pursuing a career in medical science or a related field.'
b'This is the ninth successful year of the SMaRT Program and thus far, 46 students have successfully completed this summer research internship training program.'
b'2018 SMART PROGRAM APPLICATION'
b'2018 SMART PROGRAM APPLICATION'
b'Key dates:'
b'Application deadline:\xc2\xa0 March 30, 2018 (Deadline extended from March 15 due to technical issues) Mail signed and completed SMaRT Program Application along with three (3) signed letters of reference. Recommendation letters from teachers should be in a sealed envelope with the teacher\xe2\x80\x99s signature across the envelope seal.'
b'SMaRT\xc2\xa0Program Orientation:\xc2\xa0 June 11, 2018 Selected students will begin their internship with orientation and training.'
b'SMaRT Science Forum:\xc2\xa0 August 2, 2018 Students will present their experience through interviews, oral presentations, and scientific posters.'
b'Both Thermo Fisher Scientific and the College of Medicine provide the ideal environments and opportunities for performing research in today\xe2\x80\x99s exciting biotechnology and medical industries.'
b'Please complete the application, print, sign and return by mail to:'
b'Janet Stull Snow College of Medicine Rockford Department of Biomedical Sciences 1601 Parkview Avenue Rockford, IL\xc2\xa0 61107'
b'If you have questions regarding the program, please contact Janet Stull Snow at\xc2\xa0jlss@uic.edu'
b'jlss@uic.edu'
